<title>GERMANY: TENNIS-GERMAN OPEN RESULTS.</title>
<headline>TENNIS-GERMAN OPEN RESULTS.</headline>
<dateline>HAMBURG 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Results in the German Open men's</p>
<p>tennis tournament on Thursday (prefix number denotes seeding):</p>
<p>Second round 6-Wayne Ferreira (South Africa) beat Alberto</p>
<p>Martin (Spain) 3-6 7-5 7-5</p>
<p>Sergei Brugera (Spain) beat Jeff Tarango (U.S.) 4-6 6-3 6-2</p>
<p>Jacobo Diaz (Spain) beat Paul Haarhuis (Netherlands)</p>
<p>6-2 3-6 7-5</p>
<p>Andrei Medvedev (Russia) beat 3-Richard Krajicek</p>
<p>(Netherlands) 6-1 6-1</p>
<p>7- Alberto Costa (Spain) beat Sjeng Schalken</p>
<p>(Netherlands) 6-3 7-6 (7-3)</p>
<p>9-Alex Corretja (Spain) beat Franciso Clavet (Spain)</p>
<p>3-6 6-4 7-5</p>
<p>Third round</p>
<p>Tommy Haas (Germany) beat Oliver Gross (Germany) 5-7 7-5 6-3</p>
<p>Add third round</p>
<p>Hicham Arazi (Morocco) beat 1-Thomas Muster 6-1 6-2</p>
<p>10-Felix Mantilla (Spain) beat 8-Boris Becker (Germany) 7-6</p>
<p>(8-6)</p>
<p>6-2</p>
<p>11-Alberto Berasategui (Spain) beat 5-Marcelo Rios (Chile) 6-4</p>
<p>6-1</p>
<p>Bruguera beat Ferreira 6-1 6-3</p>
<p>Medvedev beat Diaz 6-3 6-2</p>
<p>Albert Costa beat Corretja 6-4 6-4</p>
<p>2-Yevgeny Kafelnikov (Russia) beat Slava Dosedel (Czech</p>
<p>Republic) 6-2 6-1</p>
